<b>Subject:</b> I like Grog, but he's wrong about level restrictions<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1262" TARGET=_self>found this good message on eqvault pvp</A> (Nelven)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>It's an old topic at this point. The world Grog described would be ideal, but that's not what Verant has given to the PvP community. We are stuck with a severely level restricted game, and must live with a level restriction on PvP. In the future if Verant is willing to modify the PvP combat system, then it may be possible to lessen the restrictions.
<P>End of story.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
